name: Puck
description: Chuck Norris doesn't have disk latency because the hard drive knows to hurry the hell up.

name: Ross 248
description: Chuck Norris' addition operator doesn't commute; it teleports to where he needs it to be.

name: Rigel
description: Chuck Norris doesn't need to know about class factory pattern. He can instantiate interfaces.

name: Dione
description: Chuck Norris doesn't program with a keyboard. He stares the computer down until it does what he wants.

name: Europa
description: The programs that Chuck Norris writes don't have version numbers because he only writes them once. If a user reports a bug or has a feature request they don't live to see the sun set.

name: Wolf 359
description: Chuck Norris doesn't get compiler errors, the language changes itself to accommodate Chuck Norris.

name: Venus
description: Quantum cryptography does not work on Chuck Norris. When something is being observed by Chuck it stays in the same state until he's finished.

name: Triffid Nebula
description: Chuck Norris doesn't need an OS.

name: Pinwheel
description: Chuck Norris does not use revision control software. None of his code has ever needed revision.

name: Orion Nebula
description: Chuck Norris compresses his files by doing a flying round house kick to the hard drive.

name: Dumbell Nebula
description: No statement can catch the ChuckNorrisException.

name: Callisto
description: Chuck Norris never gets a syntax error. Instead, the language gets a DoesNotConformToChuck error.

name: Blackeye
description: Chuck Norris's first program was kill -9.

name: Moon
description: Chuck Norris writes code that optimizes itself.

name: Polaris
description: All arrays Chuck Norris declares are of infinite size, because Chuck Norris knows no bounds.

name: Mercury
description: Chuck Norris can spawn threads that complete before they are started.

name: Saturn
description: Chuck Norris can instantiate an abstract class.

name: Luna
description: All browsers support the hex definitions #chuck and #norris for the colors black and blue.

name: Luyten 726-8B
description: Chuck Norris's keyboard doesn't have a Ctrl key because nothing controls Chuck Norris.

name: Mars
description: Chuck Norris hosting is 101% uptime guaranteed.

name: Messier 83
description: Chuck Norris can use GOTO as much as he wants to. Telling him otherwise is considered harmful.

name: Proteus
description: Anonymous methods and anonymous types are really all called Chuck Norris. They just don't like to boast.

name: Centaurus A
description: When Chuck Norris' code fails to compile the compiler apologises.

name: Uranus
description: Chuck Norris doesn't bug hunt, as that signifies a probability of failure. He goes bug killing.

name: Ring Nebula
description: "It works on my machine" always holds true for Chuck Norris.
